H0.text: Which ex Prime Minister died at his home in Hawarden in 1898. Benjamin Disraeli

H1.text: Which ex Prime Minister died at his home in Hawarden in 1898. Robert Gascoyne-Cecil

H2.text: Which ex Prime Minister died at his home in Hawarden in 1898. Archibald Primrose

H3.text: Which ex Prime Minister died at his home in Hawarden in 1898. Gladstone

A4.text: Disraeli's last confirmed words before dying at his home at 19 Curzon Street in the early morning of 19 April were 'I had rather live but I am not afraid to die'

A5.text: Disraeli has a memorial in Westminster Abbey, erected by the nation on the motion of Gladstone in his memorial speech on Disraeli in the House of Commons

A6.text: Robert Gascoyne-Cecil, 3rd Marquess of Salisbury died in 1903

A7.text: Archibald Primrose, 5th Earl of Rosebery (1847–1929), Prime Minister of the United Kingdom

A8.text: Gladstone died on 19 May 1898 at Hawarden Castle, aged 88.

A9.text: The House of Commons adjourned on the afternoon of Gladstone's death, with A. J. Balfour giving notice for an Address to the Queen praying for a public funeral and a public memorial in Westminster Abbey.

A10.text: William Ewart Gladstone 1809–98 biography from the Liberal Democrat History Group.
